==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Goggle-eye
<hw>Gog"gle-eye`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>One of two or more species of American fresh-water
fishes of the family <fam>Centrarchid⟦ae⟧</fam>, esp.
<spn>Ch⟦ae⟧nobryttus antistius</spn>, of Lake Michigan and adjacent
waters, and <spn>Ambloplites rupestris</spn>, of the Great Lakes and
Mississippi Valley; -- so called from their prominent eyes.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The goggler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goggle-eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
